This topic describes how to install and configure Contrast Security Service Broker for Pivotal Platform

##<a id='install'></a> Install and Configure the Contrast Security Service Broker for Pivotal Platform

1. Download the product file from Pivotal Network.

2. Navigate to the Ops Manager Installation Dashboard and click **Import a Product** to upload the product file.

3. Click **Add** next to the uploaded Contrast Security Service Broker for Pivotal Platform tile in the Ops Manager **Available Products** view to add it to your staging area.

4. Click the newly added **Contrast Security Service Broker for Pivotal Platform** tile.

5. On the **Settings** tab select the **Service Plans** option to configure a service plan.
At least one service plan is required to install the Contrast Security Service Broker for Pivotal Platform tile.
The service plan configuration requires all fields as shown below.
<img src="images/contrast-config.png" alt="Contrast service plan config">

6. Click **Save**.

7. Return to the Ops Manager Installation Dashboard and click **Apply Changes** to install Contrast Security Service Broker for Pivotal Platform tile.
